{{redirect|OGEL|the character "Ogel"|Lego Alpha Team}} :''Not to be confused with: '' Oil, Gas & Energy Quarterly. {{notability|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox journal | title = Oil, Gas and Energy Law | formernames = | cover = | abbreviation = Oil Gas Energy Law | discipline = [[Law]], [[energy policy]], [[energy economics]] | editor = Kim Talus, Anas F. Alhajji, P. Andrews-Speed | publisher = Maris BV | country = | history = 2003-present | website = https://www.ogel.org | link1 = https://www.ogel.org/journal-browse-issues.asp | link1-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1875-418X | OCLC = 697271205 }} '''''Oil, Gas and Energy Law''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering all aspects of law pertaining to oil, gas, and energy in general.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ogel.org/about-ogel.asp |title=About OGEL |publisher=Maris |work=Oil, Gas and Energy Law |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref> It publishes short comments, scholarly articles, opinion pieces, and [[book review]]s.<ref name=contribute>{{cite web |url=https://www.ogel.org/contribute.asp |title=Contribute |publisher=Maris |work=Oil, Gas and Energy Law |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref> The journal was established in 2003 and is published by Maris BV.<ref>[https://www.maris.nl/publisher-of-law-journals Publishing, Maris B.V.]</ref> The founding [[editor-in-chief]] was [[Thomas W. Walde]] ([[University of Dundee]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dundee.ac.uk/cepmlp/main/html/News/ogelannounce.htm |title=New Oil Gas & Energy Law Intelligence Service |work= |accessdate=2015-06-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20040219162603/http://www.dundee.ac.uk/cepmlp/main/html/News/ogelannounce.htm |archivedate=February 19, 2004 }}</ref> The current editors-in-chief are Kim Talus ([[Tulane University Law School]])<ref>[http://www.law.tulane.edu/tlsNews/newsItem.aspx?id=21103, Kim Talus Joins Tulane as McCulloch Chair in Energy Law]</ref>, Anas F. Alhajji (Energy Economist)<ref>[https://www.anasalhajji.com/, Dr. Anas F. Alhajji - energy economist, researcher, writer and a speaker]</ref>, and P. Andrews-Speed ([[National University of Singapore]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ogel.org/editorial-team.asp |title=Editorial team |publisher=Maris |work=Oil, Gas and Energy Law |accessdate=2013-06-01}}</ref>
==OGELFORUM==
''OGEL'' hosts the archives of OGELFORUM<ref> {{cite web |url=https://www.ogel.org/ogelforum.asp |title=OGELFORUM |accessdate=2018-07-10}}</ref>, the associated discussion list. It is one of the oldest virtual energy discussion fora for discussion, sharing of insights and intelligence of relevant issues related in a significant way to oil, gas and energy issues: Policy, legislation, contracting, security strategy, climate change related to energy. It incorporates the archives of the ENATRES<ref>http://app.dundee.ac.uk/pressreleases/novcont/backups/cepml.htm~0, ENATRAS (1997)</ref> discussion list. Anas F. Alhajji is the current OGELFORUM Moderator.
