'''Silicon Savannah''' is a term used to refer to the technology ecosystem in [[Kenya]]. The term is a play on [[Silicon Valley]] and the [[grassland]] [[savanna]] ecosystem that is a dominant feature of Kenya's ecology.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Bright|first1=Jake|title=The Rise Of Silicon Savannah And Africa’s Tech Movement|url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/07/23/the-rise-of-silicon-savannah-and-africas-tech-movement/|website=TechCrunch|accessdate=27 December 2015}}</ref> It is known for producing fast growing social enterprises like [[M-kopa]] and others.<ref>https://www.ft.com/content/ccfaa1ba-d0f1-11e5-831d-09f7778e7377?mhq5j=e5</ref>
==Konza Technology City== This term became associated with [[Konza Technology City]], a planned urban development in [[Machakos County|Machakos]] and [[Makueni County|Makueni]] counties that would focus on offering services related to information technology to support tech entrepreneurs in Kenya.<ref>{{cite web|title=Silicon Savannah: Kenya's Billion-Dollar Tech Bet|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/b/fa73fc02-c511-4824-806d-5656acdfae7c|website=Bloomberg.com}}</ref>
